<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB09048</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING ARTICLE 83 OF THE PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 442, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE LABOR CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES, AS AMENDED</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : 
Intends to help ease the burden of employees in commuting to work by allowing alternative working arrangements.

Proposes to remove the limiting "normal work hours" from eight (8) hours a day for five (5) days to a more flexible work duration which means that employees may clock in to work at any time as long as they complete the required number of hours.

Proposes further to put a ceiling on the number of working hours to forty-eight (48) hours per week in order to protect the well-being of employees.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VILLAFUERTE, LUIS RAYMUND JR. F.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-02-06</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2019-02-07</td></tr></table>